HEADWORD: Bramble
<hw>Bram"ble</hw> <pr>(br⟦acr⟧m"b'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>brembil</ets>, AS. <ets>br⟦emac⟧mel</ets>, <ets>br⟦emac⟧mbel</ets>,
<ets>br⟦aemac⟧mbel</ets> (akin to OHG. <ets>br⟦amac⟧mal</ets>), fr. the
same root as E. <ets>broom</ets>, As. <ets>br⟦omac⟧m</ets>. See
<er>Broom</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant of
the genus <gen>Rubus</gen>, including the raspberry and blackberry.
Hence: Any rough, prickly shrub.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The thorny <qex>brambles</qex>, and embracing bushes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The brambling or bramble
finch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bramble bush</ent>⟦br⟧
